	<p class="cs63FD752D"><span class="csEF05ACC">&nbsp;</span></p><h4 class="cs89687900">
		<span class="csB9803513">&sect;48-13-302. Incomes below the table for determining basic child support obligations.</span></h4>
	<p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">If combined </span><span class="cs68EFC440">adjusted gross income</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> </span><a name="_Hlk219296081"><span class="cs46AE26E6">net pay</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> </span></a><span class="csEF05ACC">is below $550 per month, which is the lowest amount of income considered in the table of monthly basic child support obligations set forth in subsection (a) of this section, the basic child support obligation shall be set at $50 per month or a discretionary amount determined by the court based on the resources and living expenses of the parents and the number of children due support.</span></p><h4 class="cs89687900">
		<span class="csB9803513">&sect;48-13-303. Incomes above the table for determining basic child support obligations.</span></h4>
	<p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">If combined </span><span class="cs68EFC440">adjusted gross income</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">net pay</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> is above $35,000 per month, which is the highest amount of income considered in the table of monthly basic child support obligations set forth in &sect;48-13-301 of this code, the basic child support obligation shall not be less than it would be based on a combined </span><span class="cs68EFC440">adjusted gross income</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">net pay</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> of $35,000. The court may also compute the basic child support obligation for combined </span><span class="cs68EFC440">adjusted gross incomes</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">net pay</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> above $35,000 by the following:</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">(1) One child &mdash; $2,527 + 0.088 x combined </span><span class="cs68EFC440">adjusted gross income</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">net pay</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> above $35,000 per month;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">(2) Two children &mdash; $3,719 + 0.129 x combined </span><span class="cs68EFC440">adjusted gross income</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">net pay</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> above $35,000 per month;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">(3) Three children &mdash; $4,342 + 0.153 x combined </span><span class="cs68EFC440">adjusted gross income</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">net pay</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> above $35,000 per month;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">(4) Four children &mdash; $4,850 + 0.169 x combined </span><span class="cs68EFC440">adjusted gross income</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">net pay</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> above $35,000 per month;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">(5) Five children &mdash; $5,335 + 0.183 x combined </span><span class="cs68EFC440">adjusted gross income</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">net pay</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> above $35,000 per month; and</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">(6) Six children &mdash; $5,799 + 0.196 x combined </span><span class="cs68EFC440">adjusted gross income</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">net pay</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> above $35,000 per month.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">Part IV. Support in sole custody cases.</span></p><h3 class="cs3117C120">
